link:labelLink.link:label: Insurance Type Dimension
This dimension represents the types of insurance.
Default Cover Type Dimension
This dimension represents the types of default cover of bundled insurance where multiple types of insurance cover are provided under one premium.
Total And Permanent Disability Insurance
Represents a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only if the member is suffering permanent incapacity.
Other Insurance
Represents any other insurance not categorised in the list.
Life Insurance
Represents a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only in the event of the death of the member and which is provided by taking out insurance.
Income Protection Insurance
Represents the temporary incapacity cover provided to members, where temporary incapacity insurance cover has the meaning given in the Superannuation Industry (Supervision) Regulations.
Not Applicable
Represents the insurance type not applicable to the information reported.
Life And Total And Permanent Disability And Income Protection

Represents bundled Life, TPD (Total and Permanent Disability) and IP (Income Protection) insurance. Life insurance is a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only in the event of the death of the member and which is provided by taking out insurance. Total and permanent disability insurance is a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only if the member is suffering permanent incapacity. Income protection insurance is the temporary incapacity cover provided to members, where temporary incapacity insurance cover has the meaning given in the Superannuation Industry (Supervision) Regulations.
Total And Permanent Disability And Income Protection

Represents bundled TPD (Total and Permanent Disability) and IP (Income Protection) insurance. Total and permanent disability insurance is a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only if the member is suffering permanent incapacity. Income protection insurance is the temporary incapacity cover provided to members, where temporary incapacity insurance cover has the meaning given in the Superannuation Industry (Supervision) Regulations.
Life And Total And Permanent Disability

Represents bundled life insurance and TPD (total and permanent disability) insurance. Life insurance is a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only in the event of the death of the member and which is provided by taking out insurance. Total and permanent disability insurance is a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only if the member is suffering permanent incapacity.
Life And Income Protection

Represents bundled life and IP (Income Protection) insurance. Life insurance is a benefit, in respect of each member, that is payable only in the event of the death of the member and which is provided by taking out insurance. Income protection insurance is the temporary incapacity cover provided to members, where temporary incapacity insurance cover has the meaning given in the Superannuation Industry (Supervision) Regulations.
